  "ownership": "As for my own copy, in the year 2000 (but not part of the \"2000 collection\" you hear me talking about all the time), I obtained one of those copies that had the top third of the front cover cut off by the original selling store, to be returned to the publisher for credit, so it was in fair/poor condition, but it was still a copy of [LINK:1963:ASM_2_asm1|ASM #2], so that alone made it worth a bit.\n\n[ASSET: right | MyCopies | width=33%] About 20 years later, I found a coverless copy of issue #129 (first appearance of the Punisher) at an estate sale for less than $1.&nbsp; I bundled the two copies together in one eBay listing, which sold in March 2020 for $449, bringing in over $390.&nbsp; I had paid around $900 for the large Spider-Man collection that included the copy of #2, and in one shot, I recouped over a third of that, so I was happy -- and there were many dozens of old ASMs left in there still to sell.\n[BR]\n[BR] I'm convinced it was the bundling of the two key issues that made the sale, despite the fact that both were in poor condition.",
  "highlight": "Spider‑Man's high‑flying puzzle of the month gets solved with deduction, not fists or altitude."
}